  "analysis": "Numpy version is 2.4.0 (numpy 2.x). Indeed the error is due to numpy 2.0's stricter copy=False handling. The fasttext package uses np.array with copy=False in many places. The solution is to patch those lines to use np.asarray (or downgrade numpy). Since we are in a controlled environment, we can patch the installed package. Let's examine the file to see if we can replace all occurrences of np.array(..., copy=False) with np.asarray(...). We'll need to edit the file as root. Let's first backup and then apply sed.",
  "plan": "1. Create a backup of FastText.py. 2. Use sed to replace np.array(..., copy=False) patterns. However, the pattern may have multiple arguments. Safer to use Python to patch the file. We'll write a small script to replace lines. 3. After patching, test prediction again. If successful, fasttext should work. Also need to ensure other functions (like get_labels, etc) work. We'll run a more comprehensive test.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "cp /usr/local/lib/python3.13/site-packages/fasttext/FastText.py /usr/local/lib/python3.13/site-packages/fasttext/FastText.py.backup\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat > /tmp/patch_fasttext.py << 'EOF'\nimport re\nimport sys\npath = '/usr/local/lib/python3.13/site-packages/fasttext/FastText.py'\nwith open(path, 'r') as f:\n    content = f.read()\n# replace np.array(something, copy=False) with np.asarray(something)\n# careful about whitespace\npattern = r'np\\.array\\(([^,]+),\\s*copy=False\\)'\nnew_content = re.sub(pattern, r'np.asarray(\\1)', content)\n# also there might be np.array(y_scores, copy=False), np.array(y_true, copy=False) on same line\n# but our pattern may not capture both; we can do a more general pattern\n# Let's do a second pattern for np.array(..., copy=False) where ... may contain commas\npattern2 = r'np\\.array\\(([^)]+),\\s*copy=False\\)'\nnew_content = re.sub(pattern2, r'np.asarray(\\1)', new_content)\nwith open(path, 'w') as f:\n    f.write(new_content)\nprint('Patched', path)\nEOF\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "python3 /tmp/patch_fasttext.py\n",
      "duration": 0.1
